summary: TL*THE CONTACT OWNS A 2008 MIDWEST 2AATV UTILITY TRAILER (NA).  THE CONTACT STATED THAT THE LOADING RAMPS ON THE TRAILER WERE TOO SHORT WHEN TRYING TO LOAD THE VEHICLE.  THE LOADING RAMPS WERE 57 DEGREES FROM THE SIDE AND 59 DEGREES FROM THE REAR.  WHEN HE ATTEMPTED TO LOAD SOME ITEMS ONTO THE VEHICLE, THEY FELL BACK ON HIM.  HE FILED A COMPLAINT WITH THE MANUFACTURER.  THE CURRENT AND FAILURE MILEAGES WERE 300.  THE ENGINE SIZE, NUMBER OF CYLINDERS, AND POWERTRAIN WERE INAPPLICABLE.
